<p class=kids>When Europeans began exploring the Southern Hemisphere, they saw 
different stars, which made new patterns. They began naming Southern 
hemisphere constellations. They called one Crux, the Southern Cross. They called another 
Centaurus, the Centaur. They even named one constellation Microscopium, the microscope!</p>

